dspace-development.title: ThesisCentral users must be able to update passwords for user accounts

comments.body: Specifying an empty password does not resolve this.

```ruby

psql_statement = []

Range.new(17767, 19046).each do |person_id|
  secret = "test"

  salt = Java::byte[24].new
  random = java.util.Random.new(person_id)
  random.nextBytes(salt)
  md = java.security.MessageDigest.getInstance("SHA-256")
  md.update(salt)
  byteHash = md.digest(secret.to_java.getBytes())
  hash = java.lang.StringBuffer.new()
  Range.new(0, byteHash.length - 1).each do |i|
    hash.append(java.lang.Integer.toString((byteHash[i] & 0xff) + 0x100, 16).to_java.substring(1))
  end
  password_hash = hash.toString()

  psql_statement << "UPDATE person SET passwordhash='#{password_hash}' WHERE id=#{person_id}"
end

File.open("update.sql", 'wb') { |file| file.write( "#{psql_statement.join('; ')};" ) } 
```

...looks to produce a different password hash when using JRuby within my local environment.
This worked! I shall need to proceed by iterating over the `id` values for each account and generating the hashes.

This was just tested successfully, however the e-mail addresses need to be updated:

```
The email addresses still look like [netid@gmail.com](mailto:netid@gmail.com) and they should be thesiscentralpu+netid@gmail.com
```
This has undergone some preliminary testing, and is being offered to the reporting user for further confirmation that it has been resolved.
This was confirmed by the reporting user as resolved.

princeton_ansible.title: [Postgresql] multiple machines try to create the same database

comments.body: The task should have `run_once: true` set on it, so it only ever runs on one machine. See https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/user_guide/playbooks_strategies.html#running-on-a-single-machine-with-run-once for docs.

also, question about how this might work when MARC records are created. example: LC term "slaves" is to be changed to "enslaved people" in the catalog, using a local vocab in the 650 field (get details from Mark Z.?). Is this going to happen automatically for archival collections in the catalog? Will archivists making new FAs continue to use "slaves" to link with LC? will PULFAlight then need its own system to hide LC terms?
